1. Overview
This repository serves as the sovereign-first, POPIA-compliant retail orchestration framework, engineered for the South African market. It is designed to provide auditable, human-supervised intelligence for retail operations while maintaining strict adherence to regional data protection mandates.
2. POPIA Compliance Statement
Our commitment to the Protection of Personal Information Act (POPIA) is foundational:
Purpose Limitation: Personal information is collected only for specified, explicit, and legitimate purposes.
Data Minimization: We restrict data collection to the minimum required for the transaction.
Data Residency: All sensitive customer data is stored within secured, South African-based infrastructure.
Transparency: All automated processing is subject to human-in-the-loop oversight to ensure accountability.
3. Architecture Overview
The system utilizes a 63-agent hierarchy built on the OpenClaw environment. Key components include:
Orchestration Nodes: Managing query routing and task delegation.
Compliance Nodes: Real-time monitoring of regulatory alignment.
Integrator Nodes: Secure bridges to local inventory and payment gateways.
